    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Geth keeps all recent state in memory and garbage collects in memory. When you shut it down, all that live state data needs to be written to disk. You didn't wait for Geth to terminate gracefully, rather murdered it in the process (there's a log `Writing cached state to disk`, it's never logged success).\r\n\r\nWriting the cached state generally can take even up to a minute. Please make sure you don't murder the process while it's shutting down. If you use docker, please bump the shutdown timeout from the default 10 seconds to maybe 3 minutes.",
